{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1206,"text":"I'm driven by pure passion"},{"time":3366,"text":"to create photographs that tell stories."},{"time":6767,"text":"Photography can be described\nas the recording of a single moment"},{"time":11269,"text":"frozen within a fraction of time."},{"time":14184,"text":"Each moment or photograph\nrepresents a tangible piece"},{"time":18361,"text":"of our memories as time passes."},{"time":21547,"text":"But what if you could capture more\nthan one moment in a photograph?"},{"time":25551,"text":"What if a photograph\ncould actually collapse time,"},{"time":29222,"text":"compressing the best moments\nof the day and the night"},{"time":32164,"text":"seamlessly into one single image?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35395,"text":"I've created a concept\ncalled \"Day to Night\""},{"time":38196,"text":"and I believe it's going to change"},{"time":39847,"text":"the way you look at the world."},{"time":41308,"text":"I know it has for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43260,"text":"My process begins by photographing\niconic locations,"},{"time":47894,"text":"places that are part of what I call\nour collective memory."},{"time":51570,"text":"I photograph from a fixed vantage point,\nand I never move."},{"time":55024,"text":"I capture the fleeting moments\nof humanity and light as time passes."},{"time":59981,"text":"Photographing for anywhere\nfrom 15 to 30 hours"},{"time":62872,"text":"and shooting over 1,500 images,"},{"time":65508,"text":"I then choose the best moments\nof the day and night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69600,"text":"Using time as a guide,"},{"time":71034,"text":"I seamlessly blend those best moments\ninto one single photograph,"},{"time":75351,"text":"visualizing our conscious\njourney with time."},{"time":79431,"text":"I can take you to Paris"},{"time":81424,"text":"for a view from the Tournelle Bridge."},{"time":84342,"text":"And I can show you the\nearly morning rowers"},{"time":86480,"text":"along the River Seine."},{"time":88554,"text":"And simultaneously,"},{"time":90420,"text":"I can show you Notre Dame aglow at night."},{"time":93820,"text":"And in between, I can show you\nthe romance of the City of Light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99885,"text":"I am essentially a street photographer\nfrom 50 feet in the air,"},{"time":103201,"text":"and every single thing you see\nin this photograph"},{"time":105555,"text":"actually happened on this day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110549,"text":"Day to Night is a global project,"},{"time":112726,"text":"and my work has always been about history."},{"time":115975,"text":"I'm fascinated by the concept\nof going to a place like Venice"},{"time":119441,"text":"and actually seeing it during\na specific event."},{"time":121993,"text":"And I decided I wanted to see\nthe historical Regata,"},{"time":125450,"text":"an event that's actually been\ntaking place since 1498."},{"time":129906,"text":"The boats and the costumes\nlook exactly as they did then."},{"time":134821,"text":"And an important element that I really\nwant you guys to understand is:"},{"time":138347,"text":"this is not a timelapse,"},{"time":139845,"text":"this is me photographing\nthroughout the day and the night."},{"time":145181,"text":"I am a relentless collector\nof magical moments."},{"time":148848,"text":"And the thing that drives me\nis the fear of just missing one of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156227,"text":"The entire concept came about in 1996."},{"time":160893,"text":"LIFE Magazine commissioned me\nto create a panoramic photograph"},{"time":165142,"text":"of the cast and crew of Baz Luhrmann's\nfilm Romeo + Juliet."},{"time":170710,"text":"I got to the set and realized:\nit's a square."},{"time":174111,"text":"So the only way I could actually create\na panoramic was to shoot a collage"},{"time":178533,"text":"of 250 single images."},{"time":181391,"text":"So I had DiCaprio and Claire Danes\nembracing."},{"time":184973,"text":"And as I pan my camera to the right,"},{"time":187787,"text":"I noticed there was a mirror on the wall"},{"time":190409,"text":"and I saw they were\nactually reflecting in it."},{"time":192848,"text":"And for that one moment, that one image"},{"time":194802,"text":"I asked them, \"Would you guys just kiss"},{"time":196692,"text":"for this one picture?\""},{"time":198085,"text":"And then I came back\nto my studio in New York,"},{"time":200900,"text":"and I hand-glued these 250 images together"},{"time":204845,"text":"and stood back and went,\n\"Wow, this is so cool!"},{"time":207694,"text":"I'm changing time in a photograph.\""},{"time":210422,"text":"And that concept actually\nstayed with me for 13 years"},{"time":214636,"text":"until technology finally\nhas caught up to my dreams."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219401,"text":"This is an image I created\nof the Santa Monica Pier, Day to Night."},{"time":222880,"text":"And I'm going to show you a little video"},{"time":224833,"text":"that gives you an idea of what\nit's like being with me"},{"time":227410,"text":"when I do these pictures."},{"time":229330,"text":"To start with, you have to understand\nthat to get views like this,"},{"time":232790,"text":"most of my time is spent up high,\nand I'm usually in a cherry picker"},{"time":236543,"text":"or a crane."},{"time":237718,"text":"So this is a typical day,\n12-18 hours, non-stop"},{"time":241134,"text":"capturing the entire day unfold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244290,"text":"One of the things that's great\nis I love to people-watch."},{"time":247290,"text":"And trust me when I tell you,"},{"time":248727,"text":"this is the greatest seat\nin the house to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252226,"text":"But this is really how I go about\ncreating these photographs."},{"time":255785,"text":"So once I decide on my view\nand the location,"},{"time":259521,"text":"I have to decide where day begins\nand night ends."},{"time":262704,"text":"And that's what I call the time vector."},{"time":265476,"text":"Einstein described time as a fabric."},{"time":269257,"text":"Think of the surface of a trampoline:"},{"time":271659,"text":"it warps and stretches with gravity."},{"time":274924,"text":"I see time as a fabric as well,"},{"time":277742,"text":"except I take that fabric and flatten it,\ncompress it into single plane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283095,"text":"One of the unique aspects\nof this work is also,"},{"time":285318,"text":"if you look at all my pictures,"},{"time":286842,"text":"the time vector changes:"},{"time":288376,"text":"sometimes I'll go left to right,"},{"time":290086,"text":"sometimes front to back,\nup or down, even diagonally."},{"time":295249,"text":"I am exploring the space-time continuum"},{"time":298010,"text":"within a two-dimensional still photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301114,"text":"Now when I do these pictures,"},{"time":303042,"text":"it's literally like a real-time puzzle\ngoing on in my mind."},{"time":306750,"text":"I build a photograph based on time,"},{"time":309432,"text":"and this is what I call the master plate."},{"time":311766,"text":"This can take us several\nmonths to complete."},{"time":315126,"text":"The fun thing about this work is"},{"time":317449,"text":"I have absolutely zero control\nwhen I get up there"},{"time":320803,"text":"on any given day and capture photographs."},{"time":323218,"text":"So I never know who's\ngoing to be in the picture,"},{"time":325536,"text":"if it's going to be a great\nsunrise or sunset -- no control."},{"time":328543,"text":"It's at the end of the process,"},{"time":330385,"text":"if I've had a really great day\nand everything remained the same,"},{"time":333417,"text":"that I then decide who's in and who's out,"},{"time":336050,"text":"and it's all based on time."},{"time":337809,"text":"I'll take those best moments that I pick\nover a month of editing"},{"time":341256,"text":"and they get seamlessly blended\ninto the master plate."},{"time":346168,"text":"I'm compressing the day and night"},{"time":348487,"text":"as I saw it,"},{"time":350151,"text":"creating a unique harmony between\nthese two very discordant worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355268,"text":"Painting has always been a really\nimportant influence in all my work"},{"time":359130,"text":"and I've always been a huge fan\nof Albert Bierstadt,"},{"time":361865,"text":"the great Hudson River School painter."},{"time":363723,"text":"He inspired a recent series\nthat I did on the National Parks."},{"time":367120,"text":"This is Bierstadt's Yosemite Valley."},{"time":370347,"text":"So this is the photograph\nI created of Yosemite."},{"time":373427,"text":"This is actually the cover story\nof the 2016 January issue"},{"time":377230,"text":"of National Geographic."},{"time":379592,"text":"I photographed for over\n30 hours in this picture."},{"time":382371,"text":"I was literally on the side of a cliff,"},{"time":385044,"text":"capturing the stars\nand the moonlight as it transitions,"},{"time":389109,"text":"the moonlight lighting El Capitan."},{"time":390988,"text":"And I also captured this transition\nof time throughout the landscape."},{"time":395641,"text":"The best part is obviously seeing\nthe magical moments of humanity"},{"time":399614,"text":"as time changed --"},{"time":402831,"text":"from day into night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406072,"text":"And on a personal note,"},{"time":407634,"text":"I actually had a photocopy\nof Bierstadt's painting in my pocket."},{"time":411783,"text":"And when that sun started\nto rise in the valley,"},{"time":414055,"text":"I started to literally shake\nwith excitement"},{"time":416329,"text":"because I looked at the painting and I go,"},{"time":418631,"text":"\"Oh my god, I'm getting Bierstadt's\nexact same lighting"},{"time":422044,"text":"100 years earlier.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":425757,"text":"Day to Night is about all the things,"},{"time":428640,"text":"it's like a compilation of all\nthe things I love"},{"time":430911,"text":"about the medium of photography."},{"time":433071,"text":"It's about landscape,"},{"time":434748,"text":"it's about street photography,"},{"time":436371,"text":"it's about color, it's about architecture,"},{"time":438697,"text":"perspective, scale --\nand, especially, history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442371,"text":"This is one of the most historical moments"},{"time":444396,"text":"I've been able to photograph,"},{"time":445808,"text":"the 2013 Presidential Inauguration\nof Barack Obama."},{"time":449682,"text":"And if you look closely in this picture,"},{"time":451831,"text":"you can actually see time changing"},{"time":453932,"text":"in those large television sets."},{"time":455901,"text":"You can see Michelle\nwaiting with the children,"},{"time":458541,"text":"the president now greets the crowd,"},{"time":460424,"text":"he takes his oath,"},{"time":461700,"text":"and now he's speaking to the people."},{"time":464698,"text":"There's so many challenging aspects\nwhen I create photographs like this."},{"time":469096,"text":"For this particular photograph,"},{"time":471093,"text":"I was in a 50-foot scissor lift\nup in the air"},{"time":474732,"text":"and it was not very stable."},{"time":476050,"text":"So every time my assistant and I\nshifted our weight,"},{"time":479242,"text":"our horizon line shifted."},{"time":480804,"text":"So for every picture you see,"},{"time":482447,"text":"and there were about\n1,800 in this picture,"},{"time":484860,"text":"we both had to tape our feet into position"},{"time":487843,"text":"every time I clicked the shutter."},{"time":490010,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494202,"text":"I've learned so many extraordinary\nthings doing this work."},{"time":498868,"text":"I think the two most important\nare patience"},{"time":502297,"text":"and the power of observation."},{"time":504958,"text":"When you photograph a city\nlike New York from above,"},{"time":508384,"text":"I discovered that those people in cars"},{"time":510522,"text":"that I sort of live with everyday,"},{"time":512856,"text":"they don't look like people\nin cars anymore."},{"time":514936,"text":"They feel like a giant school of fish,"},{"time":517438,"text":"it was a form of emergent behavior."},{"time":520063,"text":"And when people describe\nthe energy of New York,"},{"time":523007,"text":"I think this photograph begins\nto really capture that."},{"time":526260,"text":"When you look closer in my work,"},{"time":528019,"text":"you can see there's stories going on."},{"time":530235,"text":"You realize that Times Square is a canyon,"},{"time":533198,"text":"it's shadow and it's sunlight."},{"time":535883,"text":"So I decided, in this photograph,\nI would checkerboard time."},{"time":539105,"text":"So wherever the shadows are, it's night"},{"time":541190,"text":"and wherever the sun is,\nit's actually day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544453,"text":"Time is this extraordinary thing"},{"time":546727,"text":"that we never can really\nwrap our heads around."},{"time":549940,"text":"But in a very unique and special way,"},{"time":551966,"text":"I believe these photographs\nbegin to put a face on time."},{"time":556703,"text":"They embody a new\nmetaphysical visual reality."},{"time":562996,"text":"When you spend 15 hours\nlooking at a place,"},{"time":566917,"text":"you're going to see things\na little differently"},{"time":569148,"text":"than if you or I walked up\nwith our camera,"},{"time":571180,"text":"took a picture, and then walked away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573175,"text":"This was a perfect example."},{"time":575175,"text":"I call it \"Sacré-Coeur Selfie.\""},{"time":577667,"text":"I watched over 15 hours"},{"time":579469,"text":"all these people\nnot even look at Sacré-Coeur."},{"time":582041,"text":"They were more interested\nin using it as a backdrop."},{"time":585106,"text":"They would walk up, take a picture,"},{"time":587958,"text":"and then walk away."},{"time":590089,"text":"And I found this to be an absolutely\nextraordinary example,"},{"time":595239,"text":"a powerful disconnect between\nwhat we think the human experience is"},{"time":599723,"text":"versus what the human experience\nis evolving into."},{"time":603922,"text":"The act of sharing has suddenly\nbecome more important"},{"time":608788,"text":"than the experience itself."},{"time":611416,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":614681,"text":"And finally, my most recent image,"},{"time":617841,"text":"which has such a special meaning\nfor me personally:"},{"time":621135,"text":"this is the Serengeti National\nPark in Tanzania."},{"time":624925,"text":"And this is photographed\nin the middle of the Seronera,"},{"time":627521,"text":"this is not a reserve."},{"time":629532,"text":"I went specifically during\nthe peak migration"},{"time":632464,"text":"to hopefully capture\nthe most diverse range of animals."},{"time":636503,"text":"Unfortunately, when we got there,"},{"time":638107,"text":"there was a drought going on\nduring the peak migration,"},{"time":640711,"text":"a five-week drought."},{"time":641886,"text":"So all the animals\nwere drawn to the water."},{"time":644503,"text":"I found this one watering hole,"},{"time":646768,"text":"and felt if everything remained\nthe same way it was behaving,"},{"time":650817,"text":"I had a real opportunity\nto capture something unique."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654325,"text":"We spent three days studying it,"},{"time":656154,"text":"and nothing could have prepared me"},{"time":657845,"text":"for what I witnessed during our shoot day."},{"time":660438,"text":"I photographed for 26 hours"},{"time":663270,"text":"in a sealed crocodile blind,\n18 feet in the air."},{"time":667340,"text":"What I witnessed was unimaginable."},{"time":669920,"text":"Frankly, it was Biblical."},{"time":671491,"text":"We saw, for 26 hours,"},{"time":673570,"text":"all these competitive species\nshare a single resource called water."},{"time":679115,"text":"The same resource that humanity\nis supposed to have wars over"},{"time":682999,"text":"during the next 50 years."},{"time":685301,"text":"The animals never even\ngrunted at each other."},{"time":689515,"text":"They seem to understand something\nthat we humans don't."},{"time":693650,"text":"That this precious resource called water"},{"time":696479,"text":"is something we all have to share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699699,"text":"When I created this picture,"},{"time":703222,"text":"I realized that Day to Night\nis really a new way of seeing,"},{"time":708127,"text":"compressing time,"},{"time":710349,"text":"exploring the space-time continuum\nwithin a photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714809,"text":"As technology evolves\nalong with photography,"},{"time":719229,"text":"photographs will not only communicate\na deeper meaning of time and memory,"},{"time":723920,"text":"but they will compose a new narrative\nof untold stories,"},{"time":730594,"text":"creating a timeless window into our world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735285,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736460,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}